%N A397726 a(0) = 0; for k = 0, 1, ..., append a(k) + r^2 and a(k) + s^2 with 0 < r < s as small as possible so as to avoid duplicates.
%C A397726 Using powers of 2 instead of squares yields A081241 prefixed by 0.
%C A397726 Using Fibonacci numbers instead of squares yields A095903 prefixed by 0.
%C A397726 A permutation of the nonnegative integers: all terms are distinct; the sequence contains 0; if all the values up to v >= 0 have appeared, v+1 necessarily appears, at the latest, as the first child of v.
